;
NUMBER 241
NAME Church Street
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
The Temple of Rorin rises up before you, it's newly raised spires gleaming in
the sunlight as they seem to scrape the heavens. A massive marble arch, veined
with amber, seems to shimmer with the power of the Sun God himself. Rorinite
Ceturions stand guard at the arch, providing protection to the temple's
faithful. A colossal stained glass window decorated in a rainbow of orange,
yellow, red and gold, forms the image of a fiery sun atop the great arch.
The sun reflects off the orb shaped window, bathing the street in a dazzling
display of colors. Across the street from the imposing temple to the Sun
God sits a half-domed building shining with a majestic aura of its own. Made
of polished white marble with muted streaks of silver flowing through the
surface, the rear of the building rises up in a fan shape with a large
engraving of the Scales of Justice engraved upon its surface. An unobtrusive
opening leads into the shrine. Two wary centurions stand guard in front of
Rorin's temple, their penetrating gaze scanning the street. Soldiers of the
Crimson Band also patrol the length of the street, their precise movements
giving due praise to the professionalism and honor of their organization.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 242
EXIT S 240
ITEM 0 350 VAL2=1190
ITEM 1 249
ITEM 2 72
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
The window is formed of concentric bands of stained glass, done in the warm
tones of gold, yellow, orange, and crimson. Seven tongues of flame, made of
pure silver encircle the orb.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GO 2
  CLEARVERB
  DISBAND
   IFVAR DISGUISED = 1
     ECHO PLAYER You are repelled from the opening as a voice booms in your mind, "You may not be hidden when standing before Justice."
     ECHO OTHERS %N is repelled from the opening.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR DISGUISED ! 1
     ECHO PLAYER You pass through the opening.
     ECHO OTHERS %N passes through the opening.
     MOVE 26
     AFFECT 26
     ECHO OTHERS %N comes through the opening.
     AFFECT 241
   ENDIF
ENDIF
CEVENT 67 10 242
  ECHO ALL The two centurions of Rorin, guarding the entrance to the temple, cast a wary eye into the street checking for any signs of trouble.
  ECHO ALL A contingent of Crimson Band guards marches past, carefully scrutinizing the street for any sign of trouble.
  AFFECT 241
  ECHO ALL A contingent of Crimson Band guards marches past, carefully scrutinizing the street for any sign of trouble.
  AFFECT 531
  ECHO ALL A few initiates of the Knights of Amilor gaze warily out at the rolling waters of the Inner Sea while they stand vigilant guard near the statue to Amilor.
;
NUMBER 1190
NAME Outer Temple, entrance
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
A grand foyer opens into the temple. A high vaulted ceiling painted with
images of the god of the sun looks down upon the entryway. A majestic arch
trimmed in gold leads into the temple proper. A hall runs off to the north,
with its entrance flanked by burly acolytes.  A stairway rimmed with fiery
runes leads upwards. An inscription has been engraved in gold onto the top
of the stairwell.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 350 VAL2=241
ITEM 1 60 ADJ1=1123 VAL2=1192
ITEM 2 706 ADJ1=312
ITEM 3 495
ITEM 4 1307
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 3
In honor of her Highness, Princess Solaria Kentaurus. Never has a Heart burned
more brightly. Never has a Spirit shone more purely. Never has a Hand served
the light so well.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXTEND 2 flecked with gold
IFVERB GO 2
  CLEARVERB
  DISBAND
  IFVAR ALIGN > 0
    ECHO PLAYER You make your way up the stairs.
    ECHO OTHERS %N makes %h way up the stairs.
    MOVE 2676
    AFFECT 2676
    ECHO OTHERS %N has entered the Solarium.
    AFFECT 1190
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER A shimmering wall of fire blocks your egress up the stairs.
    ECHO OTHERS A shimmering wall of fire appears before %N, blocking %h path.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 4
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR ORG = 11
    MOVEGROUP 1191
    ECHO OTHGROUP %N goes down the hall to the north.
    ECHO GROUP You proceed down the hallway.
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The acolytes step slightly towards the middle of the passage, blocking your way.
    ECHO PLAYER %N is barred from going into the training area.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
