NUMBER 31
NAME Temple, black gate
ASTRAL
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
The dim light spilling down the stairs is unsuccessful in penetrating the
gloom that flows from the interior of the black gate recessed in the far
wall. Shadowy threads of darkness twist and writhe inside the gate, their
movements a hellish approximation of chained beasts struggling to escape.
The gate itself offers some comfort, being engraved with images of Rorin
and Elorna, yet you can not shake the feeling of dread that fills your
mind as you stand in this chamber. You find your gaze drawn to the
stairway that ascends to the comfort of the temple proper...
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 81 ADJ1=25 VAL2=1194
EXTEND 0 flecked with hints of gold
ITEM 1 68 ADJ1=25
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Made of solid gold and silver the gate should gleam with brilliance, but
the darkness it holds back mutes the light and nearly overcomes it. You
are struck by the sense that the barrier to whatever world lies beyond is
barely holding and wonder what horrors would escape if the gate were to
shatter. You are somewhat reassured by the graven images of Rorin and
Elorna, their hands clasped together and their wills bent to the task of
holding the gate.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The faint, blood-curdling sounds of agonized screams emanates from the gate.
  ECHO OTHERS %N looks towards the gate, a nervous smile playing over %h lips.
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER The rotting stench of the grave flows from within the confines of the gate making your nose wrinkle with distaste.
  ECHO OTHERS %N looks towards the gate, %h nose wrinkling in distaste.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER There is no reason for you to pass into the gate.
   ECHO OTHERS %N moves towards the gate but then steps back.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 32
NAME Inner Temple, Kitchen
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
The clatter of pots and the smells of freshly cooked food mix with the
sounds and smells of nature that flow down from the white marble stairway
in the west wall. The chamber itself is kept in immaculate shape and the
young acolytes who have duty in the kitchens are kept in line under the
watchful gaze of the temple cook, Brother Darsos.
*DESCRIPTION_END
