NUMBER 33
NAME Inner Temple, sunken garden
ASTRAL
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is a massive sunken garden, its rich green foliage fills a circular path
that surrounds a great round Tower. Flowers of all shapes and color accent the
silver birch and white ash trees. Interlaced branches bound with flowering
creepers form a colorful canopy reminiscent of the stained glass windows in
the temple proper. A watercourse spills into a series of small ponds, each
pouring over into the next. A giant brass sundial sits in front of the massive
tower, gleaming in the sunlight. Rosewood arches lead off in all directions,
like rays from the sun. In front of each arch is a white marble statue.
Overhead, you can see the window of the Solarium, the brilliant light from
within it spilling beautifully across the demesne of the garden.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 1226 ADJ1=347 ADJ2=187 VAL2=32
ITEM 1 346
EXTEND 1 of Solaria
ITEM 2 346
EXTEND 2 of Dainon
ITEM 3 346
EXTEND 3 of Orlin
