;[OK, from here there will be a door leading into the Tower of the High Priest.
;There will also be a bunch of arches like in the quest under the Temple,
;leading N, S, E,and W, etc, bu will be accessed by Go 1 Arch, go two arch, go
;2 arch, etc.... An arch will lead to each different branch, complete with a trai
;ning area and office for
;the leader, while the other arches will lead to a shrin for Elorna, an armory,
;and a mini Arena. A stairway shoul lead back down into the kitchen.]
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
The beautiful visage of the fiery Princess Solaria gazes out across the
garden. Her hands are clenched around a golden greatsword, her body
clad in gleaming platemail with the sun of Rorin emblazoned across the
breastplate. A platinum plaque at the base of the statue reads,
"Her highness, Princess Solaria Kentaurus. She gave all her life so that
the light should never fade."
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
The stern gaze of Sir Dainon Stormblighter, his likeness captured at the
moment of his glory, looks back at you. A large demon cowers before him
as his blade strikes deeply into the heart of the darkness. A plaque at
the base of the statue reads, "Sir Dainon Stormblighter, Knighted by King
Frederick Kentaurus III. He gave all so that others might live."
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 3
The statue depicts Orlin Thinvar, one of Fayd's greatest heroes. His eyes
gaze up to the Sun, as he proudly holds the mighty sword Sunstrike between
his massive hands. An albescent plaque at the base of the statue reads, "Lord
Orlin Thinvar, Faydian Savior, Bane of Malthesia."
*DESCRIPTION_END
;[Look 4 State : A statue of Elrona...or you can pop another Rorinite hero that
;you might want to include in history or quest...up to you.]
IFVERB LISTEN -1
   ECHO PLAYER The water seems to sing as it runs its course, chanting the melody of nature's heart wrenching beauty, brought to life by the golden sun.
   ECHO OTHERS %N listens intently to the sounds of the garden.
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
   ECHO PLAYER A gentle breeze floas through the garden, carrying a myriad bouquet of floral scents.
   ECHO OTHERS %N inhales deeply of the garden's delights.
ENDIF
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 4
A school of red cap orandas wend their way silently through the undergrowth
of plants and lichen at the base of the pool.
*DESCRIPTION_END
