NUMBER 34
NAME Inner Temple, library
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
Polished mirmach bookshelves, with the flame of Rorin carefully etched
into their sides, line the stone walls of this chamber. Ancient volumes
and dusty scrolls fill the shelves, causing them to groan under the
collected weight. Large wooden tables are arranged around a statue of
Rorin in the center of the room, offering a place for the more scholarly
brethren to contemplate the knowledge that surrounds them. A golden arch
leads back out to the temple proper.
*DESCRIPTION_END
